SIMPLE: restless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Restless
<hw>Rest"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>restle⟦aacute⟧s</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Never resting;
unquiet; uneasy; continually moving; <as>as, a <ex>restless</ex>
child</as>.</def> <au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Restless</xex>
revolution day by day.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not satisfied to be at rest or in peace; averse to
repose or quiet; eager for change; discontented; <as>as,
<ex>restless</ex> schemers; <ex>restless</ex> ambition;
<ex>restless</ex> subjects</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Restless</xex> at
home , and ever prone to range.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Deprived of rest or sleep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Restless</qex> he passed the remnants of the night.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Passed in unquietness; <as>as, the patient has had a
<ex>restless</ex> night</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Not affording rest; <as>as, a <ex>restless</ex>
chair</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Restless thrush</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Grinder</er>, 3.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unquiet; uneasy; disturbed; disquieted;
sleepless; agitated; unsettled; roving; wandering.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rest"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>-
<wf>Rest"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Restorable</ent>⟦br⟧
